import React from 'react';
import { BrowserRouter as Router, Route, Routes } from 'react-router-dom';
import {
  Recruiter,
  BookmarkedFreelancer,
  AddBookmarkFreelancer,
  FindBookmarkFreelancerById,
  ListBookmarks,
  ListFreelancers,
  Job,
  AddJob,
  FindJobById,
  FindJobBySkill,
  ListAllJobs,
  AwardJob,
  ListApplicants,
  Feedback,
  AddFeedback
} from './RecruiterModule'; // Adjust path as needed

const RecruiterRouting = () => {
  return (
    <Router>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Recruiter />} />
        <Route path="/bmark/freelancer" element={<BookmarkedFreelancer />}>
          <Route path="listFreelancers" element={<ListFreelancers />} />
          <Route path="add" element={<AddBookmarkFreelancer />} />
          <Route path="find/:id" element={<FindBookmarkFreelancerById />} />
          <Route path="list" element={<ListBookmarks />} />
        </Route>
        <Route path="/jobs" element={<Job />}>
          <Route path="create" element={<AddJob />} />
          <Route path="findSkill/:skill" element={<FindJobBySkill />} />
          <Route path="findSkill/:id" element={<FindJobById />} />
          <Route path="list" element={<ListAllJobs />} />
          <Route path="award/:jobId" element={<AwardJob />} />
          <Route path="viewApps/:jobId" element={<ListApplicants />} />
        </Route>
        <Route path="/feedbacks/:frId" element={<Feedback />} />
        <Route path="/feedbacks/add/:frUName" element={<AddFeedback />} />
      </Routes>
    </Router>
  );
};

export default RecruiterRouting;
